SIMPLE: omit
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Omit
<hw>O*mit"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Omitted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Omitting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>omittere</ets>,
<ets>omissum</ets>; <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er> + <ets>mittere</ets>
to cause to go, let go, send. See <er>Mission</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To let go; to leave unmentioned; not to insert or name; to
drop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These personal comparisons I <qex>omit</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To forbear or fail to perform or to make use of; to
leave undone; to neglect; to pass over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her father <qex>omitted</qex> nothing in her education that might
make her the most accomplished woman of her age.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Omittance</ent>⟦br⟧
